Atomic Electron Populations, Localization and Delocalization Data:
-----------------------------------------------------------------
  N(A) = Average Number of Electrons in Atom A
  LI(A) = Electron Localization Index of Atom A = Average Number of Electrons Localized in Atom A
  %Loc(A) = 100 * LI(A) / N(A)
          = Percentage of Average Number of Electrons in Atom A that are Localized in Atom A
  DI(A,A')/2 = Electron Delocalization Index of Atom A = Average Number of Electrons in Atom A
               that are Delocalized (Shared) Between Atom A and Other Atoms of Molecule
             = N(A) - LI(A)
  %Deloc(A,A') = 100 * (DI(A,A')/2) / N(A)
               = Percentage of Average Number of Electrons in Atom A That are Shared With Other
                 Atoms of Molecule
Note:  ECP-Modeled Core Electrons are NOT Included Here
